  "body": "Description\r\nGot RPC error when used Remix interact to smart contract, I start new network from \"https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/Tutorials/Private-Network/Create-Private-Clique-Network/\" and then use Remix deploy my contract to the network. everything is work except use Remix interact to the smart contract because Remix will throw an error when clicking on any functions. But it works when I use web3 to connect the smart contract ABI and call it.\r\n\r\nVersion\r\nBesu: 21.1.7\r\nMetamask: 9.6.1\r\nRemix: https://remix.ethereum.org/\r\n\r\nSteps to Reproduce\r\n- Start a network using Hyperledger besu (Clique)\r\n- Connect Matamsk to the local network(:8545) - besu client\r\n- Change Remix ENVIRONMENT to Injected Web3\r\n- Use Remix Deploy an ERC20 smart contract\r\n- Wait till transaction confirm\r\n- Call the function(any function) \r\n\r\nExpected behavior: To see the result of views function or do the logic of contract\r\n\r\nActual behavior: Got error show on Remix console ex. \r\n{\r\n  \"jsonrpc\" : \"2.0\",\r\n  \"id\" : 1194539852,\r\n  \"error\" : {\r\n    \"code\" : -32602,\r\n    \"message\" : \"Invalid params\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n                                                                              \r\nFrequency: 100%\r\n",
